<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-07-11T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-07-11T16:00:00-05:00" n="556" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2146: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Ruddock</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-11T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 11,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>192. Your telegram 249, July 8, 6 p.m.<note n="12" xml:id="d556fn12">See
                                telegram no. 238, July 9, from the Chargé in Japan, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi></note></p>
                        <p>Impress upon Chinese Government inadvisability of authorizing any
                            financial commitments which would alter status of rights and interests
                            in Chinese Eastern Railway.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>